{"id":2575,"global_id":"Z2lkOi8vaGFja2Vyb25lL1JlcG9ydC8yNTc1","url":"https://hackerone.com/reports/2575","title":"Slack OAuth2 \"redirect_uri\" Bypass ","state":"Closed","substate":"resolved","readable_substate":"Resolved","created_at":"2014-03-01T15:12:55.080Z","submitted_at":"2014-03-01T15:12:55.080Z","is_member_of_team?":false,"reporter":{"disabled":false,"username":"prakharprasad","url":"/prakharprasad","profile_picture_urls":{"small":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/4Qcsaci6HdNLQCPM7oBdhJYY/3afcb5c896247e7ee8ada31b1c1eb8657e22241f911093acfe4ec7e97a3a959a"},"is_me?":false,"cleared":true,"hackerone_triager":false,"hacker_mediation":false},"team":{"id":69,"url":"https://hackerone.com/slack","handle":"slack","profile_picture_urls":{"small":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/000/069/683fee312381bc46cadc7ea1950abc87944d12c3_original.png/3afcb5c896247e7ee8ada31b1c1eb8657e22241f911093acfe4ec7e97a3a959a","medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/000/069/683fee312381bc46cadc7ea1950abc87944d12c3_original.png/eb31823a4cc9f6b6bb4db930ffdf512533928a68a4255fb50a83180281a60da5"},"permissions":[],"submission_state":"open","default_currency":"usd","awards_miles":false,"offers_bounties":true,"state":"public_mode","only_cleared_hackers":false,"profile":{"name":"Slack","twitter_handle":"slackhq","website":"https://slack.com","about":"All your team communication in one place, instantly searchable, and available wherever you go."}},"has_bounty?":true,"in_validation?":false,"rejected_anc_report_that_can_be_sent_back_to_anc_triagers?":false,"can_view_team":true,"can_view_report":true,"is_external_bug":false,"is_published":false,"is_participant":false,"stage":4,"public":true,"visibility":"full","cve_ids":[],"singular_disclosure_disabled":false,"disclosed_at":"2014-05-29T22:15:44.983Z","bug_reporter_agreed_on_going_public_at":"2014-05-29T22:15:44.657Z","team_member_agreed_on_going_public_at":null,"comments_closed?":false,"facebook_team?":false,"team_private?":false,"vulnerability_information":"Hi,\r\n\r\nI've found a way to circumvent redirect_uri restrictions imposed by the web application using domain-suffix/subdomain technique.\r\n\r\nI created an OAuth application under https://api.slack.com/applications/new. That has OAuth redirect_uri configured to http://www.google.com.\r\n\r\nSo technically \r\n\r\nAllowed Request shall be :\r\nhttps://slack.com/oauth/authorize?client_id=2190698099.2192071336\u0026redirect_uri=http://www.google.com\r\n\r\nDenied Request shall be:\r\n\r\nhttps://slack.com/oauth/authorize?client_id=2190698099.2192071336\u0026redirect_uri=http://www.blahblah.com\r\n\r\nSurprisingly If I point the redirect_uri to http://www.google.com.mx (see .mx suffix) the endpoint will be accepted, infact endpoint like http://www.google.com.attacker.com will be accepted too. The server doesn't block these suffix attacks.\r\n\r\nSo attackers can craft an OAuth endpoint like below to circumvent redirect_uri restrictions :\r\n\r\nhttps://slack.com/oauth/authorize?client_id=2190698099.2192071336\u0026redirect_uri=http://www.google.com.mx\r\n\r\n\r\nThanks!\r\nPrakhar Prasad","vulnerability_information_html":"\u003cp\u003eHi,\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eI\u0026#39;ve found a way to circumvent redirect_uri restrictions imposed by the web application using domain-suffix/subdomain technique.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eI created an OAuth application under \u003ca title=\"https://api.slack.com/applications/new\" href=\"/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Fapi.slack.com%2Fapplications%2Fnew\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ehttps://api.slack.com/applications/new\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e. That has OAuth redirect_uri configured to \u003ca title=\"http://www.google.com\" href=\"/redirect?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ehttp://www.google.com\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eSo technically \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAllowed Request shall be :\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ca title=\"https://slack.com/oauth/authorize?client_id=2190698099.2192071336\u0026amp;redirect_uri=http://www.google.com\" href=\"/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Fslack.com%2Foauth%2Fauthorize%3Fclient_id%3D2190698099.2192071336%26redirect_uri%3Dhttp%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ehttps://slack.com/oauth/authorize?client_id=2190698099.2192071336\u0026amp;redirect_uri=http://www.google.com\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eDenied Request shall be:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca title=\"https://slack.com/oauth/authorize?client_id=2190698099.2192071336\u0026amp;redirect_uri=http://www.blahblah.com\" href=\"/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Fslack.com%2Foauth%2Fauthorize%3Fclient_id%3D2190698099.2192071336%26redirect_uri%3Dhttp%3A%2F%2Fwww.blahblah.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ehttps://slack.com/oauth/authorize?client_id=2190698099.2192071336\u0026amp;redirect_uri=http://www.blahblah.com\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eSurprisingly If I point the redirect_uri to \u003ca title=\"http://www.google.com.mx\" href=\"/redirect?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com.mx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ehttp://www.google.com.mx\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e (see .mx suffix) the endpoint will be accepted, infact endpoint like \u003ca title=\"http://www.google.com.attacker.com\" href=\"/redirect?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com.attacker.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ehttp://www.google.com.attacker.com\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e will be accepted too. The server doesn\u0026#39;t block these suffix attacks.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eSo attackers can craft an OAuth endpoint like below to circumvent redirect_uri restrictions :\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca title=\"https://slack.com/oauth/authorize?client_id=2190698099.2192071336\u0026amp;redirect_uri=http://www.google.com.mx\" href=\"/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Fslack.com%2Foauth%2Fauthorize%3Fclient_id%3D2190698099.2192071336%26redirect_uri%3Dhttp%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com.mx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ehttps://slack.com/oauth/authorize?client_id=2190698099.2192071336\u0026amp;redirect_uri=http://www.google.com.mx\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThanks!\u003cbr\u003e\nPrakhar Prasad\u003c/p\u003e\n","bounty_amount":"100.0","formatted_bounty":"$100","weakness":{"id":27,"name":"Improper Authentication - Generic"},"original_report_id":null,"original_report_url":null,"attachments":[],"allow_singular_disclosure_at":"2014-04-12T01:09:34.153Z","allow_singular_disclosure_after":-211953857.35883707,"singular_disclosure_allowed":true,"vote_count":5,"voters":["k0z3r0","sw33tlie","fantam1","safisec","newfolder"],"structured_scope":null,"abilities":{"assignable_team_members":[],"assignable_team_member_groups":[]},"can_edit_custom_fields_attributes":false,"activities":[{"id":10669,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::BugTriaged","message":"Good catch!","markdown_message":"\u003cp\u003eGood catch!\u003c/p\u003e\n","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2014-03-01T20:40:36.701Z","updated_at":"2014-03-01T20:40:36.701Z","actor":{"username":"iamcal","cleared":false,"url":"/iamcal","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"ht